The difficulties are already starting to appear. I'm probably going to have a lot of trouble getting a medical certificate, due to the FAA's stance on certain medications.
Not impossible, but it's going to take ENORMOUSLY amount of time and require A LOT of extra work.
Even though it's discouraging, it's just another problem to deal with, and for now, it seems *completely* surmountable. It's just that it's going to take a lot of time and $$
In case the challenge that awaits me interests you.
The FAA isn't a fan of ADHD. They don't issue a medical certificate if you're on treatment for it.
